# owner: cross-platform-support
# Enforce LF line endings on checkout across platforms (cross-platform-support
# spec). Prevents CRLF from entering working files on Windows checkouts, which
# would break CRLF-sensitive parsers (e.g. generate-register.sh frontmatter
# fences) and produce spurious diffs. text=auto lets git auto-detect text vs
# binary; eol=lf forces LF for detected text files on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary safelist: never apply eol normalization to these, in case git's
# auto-detection mis-classifies one as text (which would corrupt it on
# checkout). Extend this list when a new binary file type enters the repo.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
